Sentencas: PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+delta (PBSCF) (X = 0, 0.3, 0.4, and 0.5) is investigated as cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Effect of Fe doping on the performance of suspension plasma-sprayed PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Suspension plasma spraying is used as a low cost and large-scale manufacturing process to prepare PBSCF cathodes.
Titulo: Effect of Fe doping on the performance of suspension plasma-sprayed PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Fe substitution effects on the crystal structure and electrochemical performance are characterized.
Titulo: Effect of Fe doping on the performance of suspension plasma-sprayed PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All plasma-sprayed PBSCF cathodes exhibit a pure and stable cubic structure.
Titulo: Effect of Fe doping on the performance of suspension plasma-sprayed PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The suspension plasma-sprayed PBSCF deposits show a porous and fine structure, and the microstructures are insensitive to Fe substitution.
Titulo: Effect of Fe doping on the performance of suspension plasma-sprayed PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Subsequent to Fe doping, the polarization resistance of PBSCF cathodes rapidly decreases for increasing Fe substitution concentration from 0 to 0.4.
Titulo: Effect of Fe doping on the performance of suspension plasma-sprayed PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Further increase of the Fe doping concentration increases the cathode polarization instead.
Titulo: Effect of Fe doping on the performance of suspension plasma-sprayed PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
